+### kind:clone with a noisy git wrapper
+
+A git wrapper on PATH may write progress to stdout even with `--quiet`. That
+output must not leak into the generated script, while real diagnostics must
+remain visible on stderr.
+
+```zsh
+% function git { [[ $1 == clone ]] && print "NOISY-GIT: progress leaked to stdout"; mockgit "$@" }
+% antidote-script fakeuser/fakerepo 2>/dev/null | subenv ANTIDOTE_HOME
+fpath+=( "$ANTIDOTE_HOME/fakeuser/fakerepo" )
+source "$ANTIDOTE_HOME/fakeuser/fakerepo/fakerepo.plugin.zsh"
+% antidote-script --kind clone bar/zzz 2>&1 1>/dev/null
+# antidote cloning bar/zzz...
+NOISY-GIT: progress leaked to stdout
+% t_reset
+%
+```
+
